the N.Y. World will want me, and I don't w^ant it either. It doesn't even seem inviting, and I have no hankering to go to New York. She said "I'm not telling you what you ought to do; I'm telling you what you will do". She said that in the new job, at first, I'd feel that I'd gambled my last cent, but that I'd win and be glad I took the plunge. Also, she saw greater and greater success. 
Keep yourself in good shape, Mamma. There are many years for you yet if you only think so. Don't let the notion get fixed in your mind that you necessarily have few years. That's not so. It's only your body that's getting older, and your mind is what matters most. Don't let that change. I judge that it isn't changing. I wnat ot have you see some of the moves that are coming yet in the Big Game as it concerns myself. You'll enjoy that. And you will see, too. 
Endless love,
Jno. 
